## 🎨 STYLING RULES

### NO GRADIENTS - EVER (Unless User Explicitly Requests)
**CRITICAL:** NEVER use gradients on your own. Only use if user explicitly says "use gradient".

```tsx
// ❌ FORBIDDEN - Never use gradients automatically
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);

// ✅ CORRECT - Always use solid colors from theme
background: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.palette.primary[600]};
```

**RULE:**
- ❌ Do NOT use gradients for ANY element
- ✅ ONLY use if user explicitly requests
- ✅ Always use solid colors from theme tokens

### ALWAYS USE MODAL AND DRAWER COMPONENTS
**CRITICAL:** NEVER create custom modal or drawer components.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use Lean IDS Modal
import { Modal } from '@lean-ids/components';
<Modal isOpen={isOpen} onClose={onClose} title="Dialog">{content}</Modal>

// ✅ CORRECT - Use Lean IDS Drawer
import { Drawer } from '@lean-ids/components';
<Drawer isOpen={isOpen} onClose={onClose} title="Panel">{content}</Drawer>

// ❌ WRONG - Custom implementation
const CustomModal = () => <div className="modal">...</div>;

// ❌ WRONG - External library
import Modal from 'react-modal';
```

